**Steps to Reproduce**:

Compile the following code:
```cs
class C1 : System.IEquatable<int?>
{
  static void M1(C1 c1)
  {
    if (c1.Equals(null))
    {
      _ = c1.ToString(); // CS8602 dereference of a possibly null reference
    }
  }
  
  static void M2(C1 c1)
  {
    if (c1.Equals(default))
    {
      _ = c1.ToString(); // no warnings
    }
  }

  static void M3(C1 c1)
  {
    if (c1.Equals(default(int?)))
    {
      _ = c1.ToString(); // no warnings
    }
  }
  
  static void M4(C1 c1)
  {
    if (c1.Equals())
    {
      _ = c1.ToString(); // no warnings (same with 'default' and 'default(int)' optional parameter values
    }
  }

  public bool Equals(int? other = null) => false;
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:
Warnings for `c1.ToString()` in every method.
All the methods are exactly the same.

**Actual Behavior**:
`M1` has a warning but other methods don't

